Package: TVSR
Title: Codes for Time-Varying Spatial Regression Estimations
Version: 0.1.3
Authors@R: 
    person("Benjamin", "Peeters", , "benjaminpeeters@protonmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5095-2021"))
Description: Implementation of time-varying spatial regression models with
    two complementary approaches to modelling dynamics in the
    spatial-dependence coefficient. Local-Kernel Spatial Regression (LKSR)
    is a semi-parametric procedure that maximises a kernel-weighted local
    log-likelihood. Score-Driven Spatial Regression (SDSR) parameterises
    the spatial-dependence coefficient as a score-driven autoregressive
    recursion in the spirit of Blasques et al. (2016). Originally
    developed to study international monetary spillovers 1980-2020; see
    Peeters and Girard (2026) <https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=6589023>.
Author: Benjamin Peeters [aut, cre] (ORCID: <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5095-2021>)
